<title>Tools: a note</title>
<summary>About tools, implements and artefacts used by the |xam. These include a brush called<i> |ku</i>, made of <i>|gipp</i> (striped jackal) hair, and its uses; a gemsbok&apos;s rib used for peeling and eating<i> |kui</i>, and its markings. An ostrich bone is used for piercing mats and baskets; the making and use of a pipe made of kid&apos;s bone; a woman&apos;s digging stick made from the <i>!kwa !kwa</i> tree, the point made of a springbok&apos;s horn and used for digging as well as stirring the fire. A digging stick is thrust into a bored stone.</summary><comments>1) Date on p.1122v (note added): &apos;K.J. 22 Oct 1879&apos; (&apos;K.J&apos; refers to Klein Jantje or |hanâ‰ kass&apos;o), 2) This story is found in Book 12 (XII)</comments><date>October 1872</date><storypages>1121opp, 1121v-1124v</storypages><category>Custom and daily life</category><category>Artefact and dress</category><author>||kabbo (Jantje) (II)</author><keyword><kw>tools</kw><subkw>and implements and artefacts used by the |xam</subkw></keyword>
